<p>
    HTML is the foundation and the structure of the house.  Without it, there would be no house at all!  CSS is the paint and other things added to make the house look nice.  Without it, the house would be boring and look bad.  JavaScript is the pipes and wiring in the house.  Without it, the house would be there and you could live in it, but there wouldn’t be very many things it could do.

    Using all three languages is important to make your websites interesting and fun, but in these lessons you’re only going to learn HTML and CSS.  So let’s get started!
</p>

